tool.name: DisplayGeodataTool

param.name: geodata_table
param.dialogReference: This is the input table, usually the results table generated by the ‘Geodata > Search’ tool, but it can be any table with a field containing the full path to the geodata you want to load into ArcMap. If the Input Table is a DBF, or a table in an ESRI File Geodatabase, then you can select a subset of rows in ArcMap and only those rows will be processed by the tool.

param.name: geodata
param.dialogReference: Select the field from the 'Table for Geodata' that contains the full path to the geodata items you want displayed in ArcMap.

tool.summary:
This tool will load all the geodata, listed in the input table selected in 'Table for Geodata', into your ArcMap display frame.
